SEC. 14

.

Post Scholarship Incentives.

â In order to encourage graduates of the scholarship program under this Act to serve in fulfillment of their service obligation and entice them to continue to stay and serve in the country even beyond their service obligation, they shall be entitled to the following incentives:

priority for job placement in the Government or in the private sector in positions appropriate to their area of education or training;

grants-in-aid and access to government research facilities in the conduct of research and development projects and other service and technology activities;

access to credit with liberal terms from government banks and financial institutions;

payment of hardship and/or hazard allowance to those who are engaged in research and other science and technology activities that posed danger and caused hardship to their well-being; and

travel and accident insurance coverage.
